# CODEOWNERS — Define code ownership and required reviewers
#
# Each line defines a file pattern and the GitHub team(s) or user(s) who
# must approve changes to matching files.
#
# Order matters: later rules override earlier ones.
#
# Docs: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
#
# ============================================================================
# HOW TO USE:
#   1. Copy this file to .github/CODEOWNERS in your repository.
#   2. Replace @org/team-name with your actual GitHub organization and teams.
#   3. Enable "Require review from Code Owners" in branch protection rules.
# ============================================================================

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# DEFAULT: Catch-all rule — applies to all files not matched below
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
*                                   @org/data-science-team

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CORE BUSINESS LOGIC — Requires senior engineer review
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
src/my_project/core/                @org/ds-senior-engineers
src/my_project/models/              @org/ds-senior-engineers

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# API LAYER — Requires backend + DS review
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
src/my_project/api/                 @org/backend-team @org/ds-senior-engineers

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# DATA LAYER — Data engineering owns schemas and loaders
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
src/my_project/data/                @org/data-engineering
data/                               @org/data-engineering
data/dictionaries/                  @org/data-engineering @org/data-science-team

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# DOCUMENTATION — Tech leads review all documentation changes
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
docs/                               @org/ds-tech-leads
*.md                                @org/ds-tech-leads
mkdocs.yml                          @org/ds-tech-leads

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CI/CD AND INFRASTRUCTURE — Platform team owns pipelines
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
.github/                            @org/platform-team
.github/workflows/                  @org/platform-team
Dockerfile                          @org/platform-team
docker-compose*.yml                 @org/platform-team

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# PROJECT CONFIGURATION — Senior engineers approve config changes
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
pyproject.toml                      @org/ds-senior-engineers
.pre-commit-config.yaml             @org/ds-senior-engineers
setup.cfg                           @org/ds-senior-engineers
.env.example                        @org/ds-senior-engineers

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# SECURITY-SENSITIVE — Require security + senior review
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
**/auth/                            @org/security-team @org/ds-senior-engineers
**/security/                        @org/security-team @org/ds-senior-engineers
